for scheduled tasks in linux we can use "crontab" service
there are following modes of it's usage:

"crontab -l" to get information about existing scheduled file
"crontab -r" to delete existing scheduled file
"crontab -e" to edit scheduled file

Some additional information can be found here:

https://www.howtogeek.com/101288/how-to-schedule-tasks-on-linux-an-introduction-to-crontab-files/

